  "text": "Deficiency or impairment of folate metabolism is associated with hyperhomocysteinemia, hypomethylation (the decreased on carbon unit transfer to purines and pyrimidines for DNA repair and biosynthesis), DNA damage, and impaired cell proliferation, malignancies, and impaired NO production. Recent study indicates that DNA methylation is an important player in both DNA repair and gene stability. Low folate levels was related to DNA damage and global DNA hypomethylation. [CITATION_1] It has been suggested that the inactivation of DNA repair pathways, which leads to an increased mutation rate and chromosomal instability, can initiate and accelerate the proliferative process. ",
